TY  - JOUR
T1  - Turnpike Planning Horizons for a Markovian Decision Model
AU  - Shapiro, Jeremy F.
Y1  - 1968/01/01
PY  - 1968
DA  - 1968/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.14.5.292
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.14.5.292
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 292
EP  - 300
VL  - 14
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper establishes some asymptotic properties of the finite state and action space Markovian decision model. For the discounted case, a turnpike theorem is proven which states that an optimal immediate decision when the planning horizon is sufficiently large is to choose one of the decisions which is optimal when the planning horizon is infinite. An upper bound on how large is sufficiently large is given. An asymptotic property of the model for discount factors in a neighborhood of one is also developed.
AB  - This paper establishes some asymptotic properties of the finite state and action space Markovian decision model. For the discounted case, a turnpike theorem is proven which states that an optimal immediate decision when the planning horizon is sufficiently large is to choose one of the decisions which is optimal when the planning horizon is infinite. An upper bound on how large is sufficiently large is given. An asymptotic property of the model for discount factors in a neighborhood of one is also developed.
